Technologies & Tools Used
🔹Backend Framework:
✔️ Developed using Python Flask Framework
✔️ Flask is lightweight and ideal for building scalable web applications, Used for handling server-side logic, APIs, and routing
🔹Frontend Technologies:
HTML for structuring the web pages
CSS for styling, layout, and responsive design
JavaScript for better, structured, and safe client-side scripting
Improved UI/UX with clean and interactive design
🔹Database:
PostgreSQL (Postgres) used as the primary database
Integrated using Postgres.py / psycopg2 (Python library)
Efficient for handling structured data and complex queries
🔹 Portal Architecture
Followed client-server architecture
Frontend communicates with backend APIs built in Flask
Backend processes requests and interacts with PostgreSQL database
Data is fetched, processed, and returned in structured format (JSON)
🔹 Core Functionalities
📊 Data Analysis & Visualization
Portal is designed to analyze large datasets
Displays insights in structured format (tables, charts, summaries)
🔍 Filtering & Search
Dynamic filters applied using user inputs
Helps in extracting specific records based on conditions
⚙️ Dynamic Data Processing
Backend performs calculations, aggregations, and transformations
Optimized SQL queries for fast performance
🔐 Data Management
Stores and manages records securely in PostgreSQL
Supports CRUD operations (Create, Read, Update, Delete)
🔹 Working Flow of Portal
User opens the web portal (frontend interface)
User applies filters or requests data
Request is sent to Flask backend via API
Backend processes request and runs SQL queries on PostgreSQL
Data is fetched and processed (analysis, calculations, etc.)
Processed data is returned to frontend
Frontend displays results in user-friendly format
🔹 Key Features
✔️ Fast and lightweight backend using Flask
✔️ Clean and responsive UI using HTML/CSS
✔️ Safe scripting with JavaScript
✔️ Efficient database handling with PostgreSQL
✔️ Scalable and modular code structure
✔️ Real-time or near real-time data analysis
🔹 Development Approach
Designed database schema first (tables, relationships)
Built backend APIs using Flask
Integrated PostgreSQL with Python
Developed frontend interface using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript
Connected frontend with backend APIs
Tested portal with real datasets for accuracy and performance
